"title": "Car",
"URL": "https://timtianchen.wordpress.com/2025/01/21/car/",
"short_URL": "https://wp.me/s7HHqt-car",
"content": "\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">I bought a Honda accord new back in nov 2021. It was not my first choice, but back then it didn’t really matter what I wanted. There was such a shortage of everything that the dealers would email me saying they had several cars coming in and ask if I wanted one. It was totally a sellers&#8217; market except they have no inventory.  Compounding that, I had no American drivers license so Carmax wouldn&#8217;t sell me a car.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Accords are reliable, low cost to maintain and relatively not ugly. so I thought I made a good choice. But I’ve come to realize that I didn’t. Don&#8217;t get me wrong, the car is those things. But those aren&#8217;t the things I really cared about.  but I guess I had to have owned a car to realize what I wanted a car. I could say the same about buying a house. Or for that matter, running a lab at a university. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The most sensible thing may not be the best choice. The notion of mediocrity is not that sexy.</p>\n",
